They attacked us on our soil. They killed thousands of Innocent Americans...and we are wrong for going over to prevent this type of thing from happening again? <br>
<br>
Sorry I say No....we aren't!<br>
<br>
Now I have a question...<br>
<br>
Who would have thought Bush was wrong if this was done with in days or weeks after the World Trade Towers incident? <br>
<br>
Now many I know and most I have asked said. They wouldn't have thought it wrong.... He would have probably been thought a Hero...what makes this different?  <br>
<br>
We didn't rush in and start slaughtering them like they did thousands of Americans, on top of his own people there he has killed. We have given him well over a year to cooperate to stop and prevent this war. This is not even including Desert Storm.<br>
<br>
How long do we need to put up with this man to know he is <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;">Evil</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> and nothing will stop him but these actions?<br>
<br>
I for one think if we don't do anything now...we will only have to fight this war later and it will be worse then. If given enough time who knows what others weapons or plots Saddam can come up with. <br>
<br>
I have many family members serving and I will support them any chance I get.  I am proud of them and of all our Men and Women serving in any Branch of Military<br>
<br>
I am PROUD to be an American. <br>
<br>
If needed I would go over and fight to ensure my Nieces and Nephews (I don't have any kids atm... but one Day I hope) will live in a Free country, lead long full lives and have the same freedoms we take for granted on a daily basis. <br>
<br>
These same freedoms those very Men and Women serving now provide for us, the ones who fought before them and the ones who bled for them. <br>
<br>
