<br>
That war was unavoidable was clear, that Saddam is a dictator that has done unspeakable acts against his own people (mostly the kurds) is clear.<br>
<br>
Without the support of the UN this war is a vigilante action.<br>
<br>
After world war 2 the UN was formed to prevent things like that ever to happnen again, the UN is a body to steer, control and uphold international law.<br>
<br>
Now we have a problem with Iraq, a problem wich has nothing, nothing to do with 9-11, if you listen to any and all of the statements made, never is there a mention of 9-11.<br>
<br>
This is about the disarming of a country, a country wich is in defiance with internatiol law, therefore it is up to the body that steers, controls and upholds that international law to do something about it, not to any single counrty or a coalition of several countries, to put it blunt, no one country has that right.<br>
<br>
However it seems the American, British and Spanish governments have no faith in the UN and decieded to take international law up in to their own hands, instead of going trough the proper chanels.<br>
<br>
If a police officer sees a criminal that he thinks might have a weapon, that he might use, should that police officer shoot that man?<br>
Moraly that answer might differ from person to person, however in the eyes of the law it is clear, no.<br>
<br>
Once again, I think a war was unavoidable ,but not in this way or at this time. Not without the support of  the international community.<br>
This war should be fought in the name of justice, not in the name of vengeange, plaese think about that and try to put your personal feelings aside.<br>
<br>
I have great respect for the troops now deployed in Iraq and the surounding countries, in Afganistan and around the worls in charge of security. I wish them the best of luck in there mision and hope they succeed, it's the decision of the govenrments I am against, not the people on the front line. That is why Isinged this petition.<br>
<br>
p.s. Beforee anyone goes calling me an ungratefull european, it was the Canadians that liberated my village in '45 so there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :neener --><img src=http://redbox.liquidev.com/~eqp/neener.gif ALT=":neener"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
