<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:times new roman;font-size:x-small;">&quot;It is magnificent, isn't it? You see, the thing about shock... is not that it upsets some people, I think; I think that it gives others a momentary joy of liberation, as we realised in that instant that the social rules that constrict our lives so terribly are not actually very important.&quot; - John Cleese</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D7F76><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/beverquestpeople.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ciraqdasm00rf>Ciraq da Sm00rf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://atlas.imagemagician.com/images/ciraq/sm00rf.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=000066>Death Metal Cowboy</font></span><br>  Posts: 831<br> <font color=#D2EDE8>(3/20/03 7:15:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://atlas.imagemagician.com/images/ciraq/scythe.gif width=150 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Citizens' Declaration</span><hr size=1> Well, I was hoping that I would not have to reply to this thread, but after reading some of the views voice thus far, I feel I must make a few points clear.<br>
<br>
If it is not completely obvious from my following statements, I did not sign this petition.  I will address a few points made and give an explanation for my thoughts to each.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Many nations feel fear that we can seemingly topple a country's government when we feel we are in the right because we have the military force to do so.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Many nations fear that we do have the power to topple governments, this is true.  However, in no way does the United States government feel that the amount of power it controls gives them the right to anything.  With great power comes great responsibility (I love this quotation...how true it is.)  It is not our right to do so.  It is our duty to the world.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No tangible proof of a link between Saddam and Al-Queda.  Lots of circumstantial evidence but nothing concrete has yet been released to the public.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Now we have a problem with Iraq, a problem wich has nothing, nothing to do with 9-11, if you listen to any and all of the statements made, never is there a mention of 9-11<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
One thing that we must note when analyzing the reasoning behind this war is that 9-11 has never been a deciding factor.  The deciding factor is protecting the security of not only the United States, but all nations, against rogue groups and nations such as Al Qaeda and Iraq.  9-11 was just the breaking point.<br>
<br>
We do not need a concrete link between Iraq and Al Qaeda to take action against Iraq.  When Presidant Bush declared war against terrorism, he was not addressing Al Qaeda alone.  He was addressing all groups and countries that would threaten the security of the United States as well as other nations.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If a police officer sees a criminal that he thinks might have a weapon, that he might use, should that police officer shoot that man?  Moraly that answer might differ from person to person, however in the eyes of the law it is clear, no.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This anaology is off the topic at hand.  If you analyze the current situation, the analogy would be more like &quot;If a police officer sees a criminal with a large cache of weapons commit a crime, should the police officer arrest said criminal and confiscate said weapons?&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
My personal opinion towards the current situation is that this war is far over due.  Saddam Hussein has been allowed to remain in power for far too long.  I completely agree with the actions taken by Presidant Bush.  Many believe that this conflict should have been solved diplomatically.  There are many more that beleive that this situation should have been left to the UN to resolve.  Both options had been attempted for too long.  When Presidant Bush declared war on terrorism, was there a large outbreak of international protest?  No.  This war on Iraq is a continuation of that war.  Saddam Hussein is a terrorist to his own people.  His regime harms his own and endangers all neighboring countries.<br>
<br>
What is done is done.  We are at war.  Protest will not stop any current action. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D7F76><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/beverquestpeople.showUserPublicProfile?gid=axegaijin>Axe Gaijin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://web.ecomplanet.com/STOR3278/servercontent/MyCustomImages/STOR3278CustomImage0417923.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><br><TABLE STYLE=filter:Glow(color=#000000, strength=4><font color=#FFFF00> <b> Wooden Practice Horse</font></TABLE> </b></span><br>  Posts: 1020<br> <font color=#D2EDE8>(3/21/03 4:45:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.ecomplanet.com/STOR3278/servercontent/MyCustomImages/STOR3278CustomImage0179089.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Citizens' Declaration</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Well, I was hoping that I would not have to reply to this thread, but after reading some of the views voice thus far, I feel I must make a few points clear.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
